RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 89. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 40000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS OR CLAIMING PRICE $50,000. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000 Horses That Have Won Two (2) Or More Races Must Carry An Additional Two (2) LBS (Horses In For The Allowance Are Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POST FACTO stalked behind the leader on the inside, tipped out on the far turn and bid between rivals at the quarter pole and may have been struck by rivals whip but was hardly affected, took over into the stretch, showed the way into the final sixteenth and held gamely. PAULLIAC (IRE) unhurried in the beginning three then two wide, traveled outside a rival into the far turn, was on the move while angling four wide leaving the bend, fought outside rivals through the stretch and lacked the needed final kick to get by. KOLOMIO stalked the top pair two wide early, bid three deep with a quarter mile left to run, fought between rivals in the furlong grounds and got edged for second. ZIO JO settled next the fence, tipped out into the stretch, angled out further from behind rivals, tried to rally in a tight spot between rivals in the final sixteenth, managed to through but ran out of time. ZOOKEEPER bobbled leaving the gate, set the pace under pressure from outside rival, shook free past the three-eighths pole, challenged by a pair of rivals at the quarter pole, lost command into the stretch and weakened. LAMPY pressed while keen early on the first turn, continued to prompt the pace up the backstretch, failed to keep up past the three-eighths pole, dropped back around the bend and tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside, tipped out, tight between late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 96. Claiming Purse 42000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since November 3 Allowed 2 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ZIMBA WARRIOR turned his head at the start to come away last, tracked two then three wide early, bid three deep leaving the far turn, dueled into the final sixteenth with CLUB ASPEN and dug in to inch ahead late. CLUB ASPEN set the pace under mild pressure in the early stages, led clear to the quarter pole, challenged by rivals into the stretch, maintained command into the final furlong, dueled with ZIMBA WARRIOR into deep stretch and yielded grudgingly in the end. IMPOSSIBLE TASK stalked the pace from inside, got put in a bit tight by SETTECENTO on the far turn and dropped to last, tipped out in the lane and finished gamely through traffic to earn the show honors. SALTO DE TIGRE settled inside then moved to the two path around the clubhouse turn, rallied three then four wide outside the top trio into the stretch but failed to find the needed late kick in deep stretch. SETTECENTO raced up close outside the leader applying mild pressure at times, chased two wide through the far turn and into the stretch and faltered in the late stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 89. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NENE DIAMOND took a bump from outside at the start, sprinted clear early, drew away along the rail around the bend, urged right handed with a furlong left to run, switched to the left hand midstretch and held safely. GENERAL WELFARE away quickly in the beginning, chased the pacesetter two to three wide into the lane, could not threaten the winner in the late stages but managed to hold the place. BAJAN BASHERT chased outside GENERAL WELFARE up the backstretch, kept off the rail and entered the lane three to four wide and could not get by GENERAL WELFARE for second. ASHLEYS SANDCASTLE chased along the inside into and around the bend and weakened in the stretch run. IDESSIA tossed her head slightly and came away a step slow on the outside, raced in range well off the rail, exited the bend four to five wide and weakened. MISS JO'S CANDY broke a step slow and bumped with inner rival at the start, lagged behind up the backstretch, trailed three then two wide around the turn and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Nene Diamond
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, sprinted clear, drew away turn, held safely

ENTRY.NAME: Idessia
ENTRY.COMMENT: tossed head/step slow, in range, 4-5wide, weakened

BIG BEAUTY chased just out of range outside a rival leaving the backstretch, moved out three deep at the quarter pole, came back to the two path entering the stretch and closed the gap on the winner while getting outfinished for second. RACE.FOOTNOTES: KATONAH vied between rivals early, dueled inside BOOK SMART past the five-sixteenths pole, inched ahead to take control in the lane and dug in late to hold that rival at bay. BOOK SMART vied three deep to the turn, dueled outside KATONAH past the five-sixteenths pole, kept the pressure on through the lane but lacked the needed punch to get by. INDULGE bumped with outer rival at the start, settled at the back, passed a rival while saving ground around the bend, moved out in the lane and showed late effort to earn the show honors. AMERICAN CAT vied inside a pair of rivals to the turn, could not keep pace midway around the bend, angled out and chased four wide into the stretch, then weakened in the furlong grounds. SUZIE QZZ BROTHER bumped with INDULGE leaving the gate, stalked the speedy trio on the inside into the turn, eased off the rail and came four wide into the stretch and could not rally. GRAZEN SUN stalked well off the rail early on, went four wide into the turn, came five wide into the stretch and also failed to rally. STREET ART broke a step slow, traveled three wide around the turn and came up empty.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACADAMIA (BRZ) stalked five wide early then moved into the two path for the clubhouse turn, gained while angling out on the second bend, drew alongside the leader at the eighth pole and drove clear. BUZZ OF NEW YORK (IRE) bumped outer rival leaving the gate, stalked between rivals then altered to the inside, got put in tight and checked hard at the three-eighths pole, moved off the rail around the far turn, closed determinedly through the lane but had to settle for second. TIK TOK FAMOUS (GB) broke out and bumped BALLET DANCING, sped to the front and moved inside, vied with rivals into the backstretch then inched ahead to take control again, moved clear with three furlongs remaining, collared by the winner with a furlong remaining, relinquished the lead shortly after and flattened to third. BALLET DANCING took a bump from inside leaving the gate, went up to press the pace from outside then vied between, ceded command early on the backstretch, moved up again three deep, bumped with outer rival into the far turn, was closest in pursuit two wide into the stretch and weakened. GOLD FOR KITTEN stalked three deep early, bumped with BALLET DANCING while four deep into the far turn, angled into the two path around that bend and weakened. KUORA (PER) forwardly placed four deep early then went up to vie three deep into the backstretch, pressed TIK TOK FAMOUS (GB) from outside then got shuffled entering the far turn, saved ground to the stretch and also weakened. DRAMATIZER got bumped and crowded in the beginning, lagged behind and never got involved.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TECUMSEH CAROLINE bumped with outer rival at the start, settled in the two path, gained while angling four wide on the far turn, took over and kicked clear in upper stretch and held safely to the wire. LA DEUXIEME ETOILE showed speed from outside and went four wide into the first turn, moved into the two path while dueling for command, inched ahead then was headed again by DELTA WIND on the backstretch, battled through the far turn, put away inner rival entering the lane, relinquished the lead to the winner in upper stretch and stayed on well to secure second. ROSE HARBOR stalked from inside then moved out to the two path, waited behind the leaders on the far turn, went between foes in the lane and finished willingly to gain the show honors. DELTA WIND sent from the gate and moved inside while dueling for command, pressed outer rival before racing on even terms once again, fought along the rail through the far turn, lost touch entering the stretch and flattened to fourth. STARSHIP DEFIANT chased in the three path early, bid three deep at the quarter pole but faltered in the final furlong. RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 86. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: YO TIME was closest in pursuit from the two path to the far turn, challenged from outside around the bend, gained the upper hand entering the stretch, moved clear with a furlong remaining and remained strong to the wire. HERECOMEGEORGIEBOY settled outside a rival early on, moved out nearing the far turn, rallied four deep then challenged outside the top pair into the stretch, was outkicked by YO TIME in the final furlong but was clearly second best. BRONKO NAGURSKI stalked the pace from between rivals, roused on the far turn while two to three wide, moved out in the lane and nailed WORKDAY for the show honors. WORKDAY sprinted to the front and crossed over to the inside, showed the way to the far turn, challenged by YO TIME around the bend, gave up the lead entering the stretch, flattened in the furlong grounds and lost the show. STAR PROSPECT pulled on the inside while a bit rank, stalked the pace then moved off the rail at the top of the stretch, kept on through the lane while going between rivals late and missed the minor awards. SHIP AND SCAM settled on the inside, looked to gain on the far turn but ran into traffic, remained inside into the stretch and could not rally. J D'S RUDE BOY stalked the pacesetter outside a pair of rivals, got shuffled back nearing the five-sixteenths pole, chased three wide into the lane and had little left for the drive. MICKEY GOLDMILL was off slow in the beginning, traveled along the inside towards the rear, moved out on the backstretch, went five deep into the far turn, spun four wide into the lane and failed to menace. LE VRON JAMES was off slow to begin, trailed two wide early, eased on the far turn and coasted through the stretch, then walked off following the race.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pulled/rank early, stalked inside, kept on between late
